<h3 id="double-pendulum">Double Pendulum</h3>

<p>A double pendulum is probably self explanatory, itâ€™s just a 2nd pendulum attached to the mass of a pendulum. For simplicity, Iâ€™m just considering a restricted 2D case. Kinetic energy of the system is simply the sum of the kinetic energy of both masses:</p>

<span class="katex-display"><span class="katex"><span class="katex-mathml"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" display="block"><semantics><mrow><mi>T</mi><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mn>1</mn><mn>2</mn></mfrac><msub><mi>m</mi><mn>1</mn></msub><mo stretchy="false">(</mo><msup><mover accent="true"><msub><mi>x</mi><mn>1</mn></msub><mo>Ë™</mo></mover><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>+</mo><msup><mover accent="true"><msub><mi>y</mi><mn>1</mn></msub><mo>Ë™</mo></mover><mn>2</mn></msup><mo stretchy="false">)</mo><mo>+</mo><mfrac><mn>1</mn><mn>2</mn></mfrac><msub><mi>m</mi><mn>2</mn></msub><mo stretchy="false">(</mo><msup><mover accent="true"><msub><mi>x</mi><mn>2</mn></msub><mo>Ë™</mo></mover><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>+</mo><msup><mover accent="true"><msub><mi>y</mi><mn>2</mn></msub><mo>Ë™</mo></mover><mn>2</mn></msup><mo stretchy="false">)</mo><mspace linebreak="newline"></mspace></mrow><annotation encoding="application/x-tex">T = \frac{1}{2}m_1(\dot{x_1}^2+\dot{y_1}^2) + \frac{1}{2}m_2(\dot{x_2}^2+\dot{y_2}^2)\\</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class="katex-html" aria-hidden="true"><span class="base"><span class="strut" style="height:0.6833em;"></span><span class="mord mathnormal" style="margin-right:0.13889em;">T</span><span class="mspace" style="margin-right:0.2778em;"></span><span class="mrel">=</span><span class="mspace" style="margin-right:0.2778em;"></span></span><span class="base"><span class="strut" style="height:2.0074em;vertical-align:-0.686em;"></span><span class="mord"><span class="mopen nulldelimiter"></span><span class="mfrac"><span class="vlist-t vlist-t2"><span class="vlist-r"><span class="vlist" style="height:1.3214em;"><span style="top:-2.314em;"><span class="pstrut" style="height:3em;"></span><span class="mord"><span class="mord">2</span></span></span><span style="top:-3.23em;"><span class="pstrut" style="height:3em;"></span><span class="frac-line" style="border-bottom-width:0.04em;"></span></span><span style="top:-3.677em;"><span class="pstrut" style="hei